import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

# Assuming 'imports_data' is your DataFrame containing the import data.
df = imports_data

# Make sure to reset the index in case 'Recipient' is not a column.
df.reset_index(inplace=True)

# Now 'Recipient' is definitely a column and not the index.

# Remove the 'Total world import' row if present
df = df[df['Recipient'] != 'Total world import']

# Handle NaN values by replacing them with 0
df.fillna(0, inplace=True)

# Set 'Recipient' as the index
df.set_index('Recipient', inplace=True)

# Drop unnecessary columns
df_years = df.drop(columns=['1990-2023', 'Percentage', 'Sum total years', 'Percentage of total'])

# Transpose the DataFrame so that each column becomes a country and rows are years
df_transposed = df_years.transpose()

# Sort countries by 'Sum total years' in descending order
sorted_countries = df.sort_values('Sum total years', ascending=False).index.tolist()

# Determine the top importers by taking the top N sorted countries
# Replace N with the number of top importers you want to show
N = 5
top_importers = sorted_countries[:N]

# Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))  # Set figure size
for country in top_importers:
    if country in df_transposed.columns:  # Check if the country is in the columns
        plt.plot(df_transposed.index, df_transposed[country], marker='', linewidth=2, label=country)

plt.title('Top Import Values by Country from 1990 to 2023')

#create a sankey diagram from the trade register
df_filtered = df_join_deliveries[(df_join_deliveries['year'] > 1995) & (df_join_deliveries['year'] <= 2005)]
df_aggregated = df_filtered.groupby(['seller_country', 'buyer_country']).sum().reset_index()

top_sellers = df_aggregated.groupby('seller_country')['units'].sum().nlargest(5).index
top_buyers = df_aggregated.groupby('buyer_country')['units'].sum().nlargest(5).index

df_aggregated['seller_group'] = df_aggregated['seller_country'].apply(lambda x: x if x in top_sellers else 'Other')
df_aggregated['buyer_group'] = df_aggregated['buyer_country'].apply(lambda x: x if x in top_buyers else 'Other')

df_grouped = df_aggregated.groupby(['seller_group', 'buyer_group']).agg({'units': 'sum'}).reset_index()
sources = df_grouped['seller_group']
targets = df_grouped['buyer_group']
values = df_grouped['units']

labels = list(pd.concat([sources, targets]).unique())

source_indices = [labels.index(source) for source in sources]
target_indices = [labels.index(target) for target in targets]

# Create the Sankey diagram
fig = go.Figure(go.Sankey(
    node=dict(
        pad=15,
        thickness=20,
